9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1245, L.D. 1874, “An Act to Enable the
10 Maine Pilotage Commission to Oversee Pilots Operating in Portland Harbor”
11 Amend the bill by inserting after section 5 the following:
12 'Sec. 6. 38 MRSA §89, as amended by PL 2007, c. 695, Pt. B, §23, is further
13 amended to read:
14 §89. Maine Pilotage Commission members
15 The Maine Pilotage Commission, as established by Title 5, section 12004‑A,
16 subsection 40, consists of 7 members who are citizens of the United States and the State of
17 Maine appointed by the Governor as follows: Three licensed pilots who are actively
18 piloting, one member from each of the coastal zones; 2 members who are not licensed pilots
19 but are from a maritime industry that utilizes the services of pilots; one member who is not
20 a licensed pilot but has a maritime background, from a list of qualified potential appointees
21 provided by the mayor of the City of Portland and the mayor of the City of South Portland;
22 and 2 members one member representing the public who are is not a licensed pilots pilot
23 but have has a maritime background. Appointments are for 3-year terms. Appointments
24 of members must comply with Title 10, section 8009. The members of the commission are
25 entitled to compensation according to Title 5, chapter 379.
26 Sec. 7. 38 MRSA §90, sub-§1, ¶B, as amended by PL 1999, c. 355, §10, is further
27 amended to read:
28 B. Make and establish just and reasonable rates of pilotage for those vessels that are
29 subject to this subchapter;'
30 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
31 number to read consecutively.
32 SUMMARY
3333 This amendment updates the membership of the Maine Pilotage Commission. It
3344 requires one member, rather than 2 members, of the public who is not a licensed pilot but
